ij-OfferCardContent-description-description--hideOnMobile">Job Summary

PUSHTech.com is hiring a Technical Support Engineer located in European Time Zones. A person who concentrates on looking at problem situations with different perspectives until finding the solution, workarounds or different solutions to a problem. Will be responsible to research, diagnose, troubleshoot, and resolve customer issues in an accurate and timely manner. Working with a SAAS platform.

Responsibilities of the role
- Research, diagnose, troubleshoot and identify solutions or workarounds to SAAS platform issues.
- Properly escalate unresolved issues to the appropriate developer team.
- Provide prompt and accurate feedback to the customer success team or directly to customers.
- Refer to databases or external resources to provide accurate tech solutions.
- Ensure all issues are properly logged.
- Prioritize and manage several open issues at one time.
- Prepare accurate and timely reports.
- Document technical knowledge in the form of notes and manuals.
- Taking ownership of customer issues reported and seeing problems through to resolution.
- Following procedures for proper escalation of unresolved issues to the appropriate developer teams.
- Required Skills and Experience
- Excellent problem-solving and communication skills.
- Ability to provide step-by-step technical help, both written and verbal.
- Good understanding of the SAAS platform.
- Hands on experience with technologies: 
Ruby, Ruby on rails, (required)
ElasticSearch, MongoDB, PHP/Java, NodeJS, HTML, JavaScript and CSS (useful)
- Teamwork skills with a problem-solving attitude.
- Ability to diagnose and troubleshoot technical issues.
- Familiarity with remote desktop applications and help desk software (eg. Zendesk, Jira).
- BS degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, Engineering or relevant field.
 

Benefits
- Rewarding career within a remote culture company.
- Competitive remuneration, benefits and bonus packages.
- Profit from working with a talented team of entrepreneurs and very talented colleagues.
- Focused on the people who are part of the company and their quality of life.
- Goal-oriented and Flexible.
- Innovative and in continuous evolution.
- Integrated by responsible and proactive people.

Salary

- All positions have a 3 years salary plan related to each person's roles and responsibilities. 
- The Technical Support Engineer position will receive a competitive salary including bonuses and benefits depending on their location and seniority.

FOR

Are you looking forward to being a Cloud Engineer? Do you think it could be interesting to learn the top notch technologies available from Google's internal point of view? Would you like to learn every single bit of the cloud systems and how they work on the top Companies worldwide? In this case, please, keep reading, as we are looking for a talented person to join our Google Cloud team in Barcelona as a Google Cloud Support Engineer for the Google Platform Team.

Companies all around the world rely on Google Cloud! Here your main responsibility will be to provide outstanding technical support for the most prestigious Google Cloud clients. 

Here you will be providing high level technical support to Serverless and Storage products (such as relational and non relational databases, containerized applications, functions as a service, Cloud file storage systems...) among other technologies to worldwide clients, while gathering feedback to help improve the Cloud Platform products, which will boost your IT career into the next level.

Minimum requirements:

100% fluent in English.
European citizenship or work permit in Spain
Bachelor's degree in computer science, software/computer engineering, or applicable work experience.
Firm understanding of programming (Python or Java)
Previous experience as developer (academic or professional)
Experience with Linux/UNIX
Experience with relational SQL and NoSQL databases
Familiar with web protocols (HTTP, DNS, SSL/TLS etc)
Ability to research using internal knowledge bases and public facing documentation (Google Cloud Platform documentation, StackOverflow)

Desirable skills:

Familiarity with modern API technologies (OAuth,  RESTful APIs, gRPC)
Knowledge of other web-centric programming languages (Go, PHP, Node.js, Ruby, .NET)
Experience with cloud providers (Google Cloud Platform, Amazon Web Services, Microsoft Azure)

WHAT YOU WILL GET

Permanent contract
Full time position (39 hours / week) 
Salary package: 30.040€ gross/year (25.000 as base salary + 3.000 as bonus + 1.540 ticket restaurant + private health insurance valued approximately 500€)
Salary review after one year
Two months of paid training!
Learning is the key to success. Here you will have constant training + access to all the Google Cloud certifications, for free! 
You will become an expert on Cloud. You will get to know how the Cloud really works in a corporate environment. 
23 days of vacation and day off on your birthday (+ Google Days off)
Free fresh fruit and coffee 
Not everything can be working: we have Ping pong, arcade machines, pool table and foosball in the office!
Teamwork in a multicultural environment, social activities and personal development, where you and your colleagues will be working together in order to achieve the objectives and learn together.
Relocation available for new joiners from outside Catalonia! 

No dress code! You will be working in a casual environment from Monday to Friday from 9am to 6pm. In the future you might work some weeks from 8am to 5 pm or 10 am to 7 pm (according to business needs).

You will also be working one weekend every two months being extra paid in case that you do so. The weekend working shift could either be from 9am to 6 pm or from 6am to 3pm.

WHO WE ARE

Webhelp Group is a consolidated and dynamic international company providing service to the top 10 companies belonging to the IT and social networking world. We are based in the heart of Barcelona with more than 3000 employees from all over the world. On top of that, we offer an attractive environment with a great team spirit. 
 
The recruitment processes and people involved in them (both recruiters and Project Managers) will not discriminate any candidacy because of age, disability, ethnic, marital status, gender, Tecnologías y Servicios Agrarios, S.A., S.M.E., M.P. (TRAGSATEC) especializada en el desarrollo de soluciones tecnológicas avanzadas, busca incorporar a un/a Analista Programador/a para participar en un importante proyecto de un organismo público.


Funciones:		
·	Desarrollo en lenguaje Visual Basic.
·	Definición, planificación y realización de las pruebas del sistema, así como su puesta en producción.
·	Documentación técnica y funcional.
·	Gestión de bases de datos SQL.


OFRECEMOS:
-	Se ofrece contrato de duración determinada estimada de 6 meses con posibilidad de prórroga por otros 6 meses, si procede. 

-	Ubicación: posibilidad de ubicación en cualquiera de las oficinas de Tragsatec en Galicia (Ourense, Lugo, Santiago de Compostela, Pontevedra, A Coruña).


-	La inscripción y presentación de su solicitud de empleo supone la declaración responsable del cumplimiento de los requisitos recogidos en la misma, así como la veracidad de sus respuestas a las preguntas de filtrado o killer questions, que respondan en relación a la misma, pudiendo ser rechazados en caso de que se compruebe su incumplimiento o falta de veracidad.

-	Cualquier contratación de duración determinada resultante de este proceso de selección garantizará por parte del Grupo Tragsa la operatividad y el mantenimiento de los proyectos/servicios, así como, el cumplimiento de la normativa interna y la legislación laboral vigente.

-	En caso de surgir bajas en este proyecto, se podrá contactar con las personas inscritas para su cobertura con un contrato de una duración estimada en función del hecho causante.

-	Para poder participar en este proceso de selección será necesario adjuntar como anexo a la solicitud, o bien durante el trascurso del proceso de selección, la documentación acreditativa del cumplimiento de los requisitos de formación académica detallados en la oferta. La incorrecta acreditación de los documentos solicitados o la falsedad en lo indicado, supondrá la exclusión inmediata del proceso.

-	En caso de títulos obtenidos en universidades y/o centros extranjeros, se deberá adjuntar como Anexo a la solicitud certificado de homologación o equivalencia expedido por el MEFP, Ministerio de Universidades de España o Suplemento Europeo al Título (SET).

-	Con el objeto de dar cumplimiento de la Norma RRH.09 para el Fomento de la incorporación de personas con discapacidad en el Grupo Tragsa, A igualdad de condiciones, se priorizarán las candidaturas de aquellas personas que cuenten con una discapacidad reconocida y acreditada igual o superior al 33%, siempre y cuando la discapacidad sea compatible con el adecuado desempeño del puesto y se aporte durante el proceso el certificado de discapacidad acreditada igual o superior al 33%.

class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-description ij-OfferCardContent-description-description--hideOnMobile">Des de Serviclients estamos buscando un/a Responsable de Ciberseguridad en modalidad 100% remota para trabajar directamente con un importante cliente final del sector IT.

Entra las funciones a desarrollar destacamos:
·	Análisis y respuesta a incidentes y los grupos detrás de ataques dirigidos, tácticas, técnicas y procedimientos
·	Monitorización de la ciberseguridad y respuesta ante incidentes
·	Análisis con atención al detalle y orientación a soluciones para aprender y adaptarse rápidamente.
·	Capacidad para dirigir y trabajar en equipo y trabajar bien bajo presión para determinar e investigar rápidamente el alcance de los incidentes
·	Guiar con tacto a los responsables de incidentes no subordinados a través de procesos de mitigación precisos.
·	Llevar a cabo investigaciones independientes e informar sobre los resultados.
·	Capacidad para aplicar la originalidad y la creatividad en la resolución de problemas.
·	Poseer excelentes aptitudes de comunicación oral y escrita para comunicarse eficazmente en situaciones normales y de estrés.

Requisitos:
·	Más de 8 años de experiencia en Informática forense/Seguridad informática y respuesta a incidentes
·	Valorable Formación Específica en Ciberseguridad
·	Experiencia y aptitudes en informática forense/redes e IR:
-	Investigaciones digitales de respuesta a incidentes e informática forense (incluidas herramientas como SANS SFIT, EnCase, FTK, X-Ways, TSK, etc.).
-	Forense empresarial (incluidas herramientas como En Case Enterprise, EnCase Cybersecurity, GRR, F- response, Volatility, Winpmen, etc.)
-	Análisis forense de dispositivos móviles (incluidas herramientas como Cellebrite, XRY, Oxygen, etc.)
-	Análisis de malware (incluyendo herramientas como IDA Pro, Radare, OllyDbg, etc.)
-	Análisis de tráfico de red y análisis forense de redes (incluyendo herramientas como Tcpdump, Wireshark, Netwitness, etc.)
-	Análisis de registros (incluyendo herramientas como ELK, Splunk)


Valorable :
·	Conocimientos de programación: Python, Shell scripting, Ruby, Perl.
·	Tecnologías y herramientas de supervisión de la seguridad: SIEM (enVision, ArcSight, SenSage, Q1), NIDS/NIPS (Sourcefire, snort, Tipping Point)
·	Conocimientos de administración de sistemas, ingeniería de redes e ingeniería de seguridad
·	Certificaciones técnicas o profesionales como EnCE, CEH, GCIH, GCFA, CISA o CISSP, etc.
·	Inglés B2
·	Disponibilidad para viajar internacionalmente (alrededor del 25% de viajes internacionales)

Se ofrece:
·	Contratación directa por empresa final TIC
·	Trabajo en 100% remoto
·	Franja salarial: entre 70 a 80.00 euros brutos/anuales. 
·	Además política de bonus (con un bonus trimestral y otro bonus anual)
Beneficios sociales:
·	Clases de inglés
·	Sistema de bienestar con acceso ilimitado a psicólogos o coach, y  posibilidad de cara al año que viene cambiarlo por seguro médico.
·	Ayuda para la práctica de actividades deportivas.
·	Formación a nivel interno como externo: programas de mentoring técnico, seminarios y retos internos, cursos y certificaciones de SANS, plataformas para realizar cursos...</p><ul is a small but fast-growing web and mobile application development award-winning agency with 22 years of experience. Our core focus is on business applications and bespoke platform development. We currently manage projects from our UK office, serving clients predominantly in the London area. The development team is at the Barcelona office. This role would be based in Barcelona
We are looking to recruit a junior developer to join our team of developers with experience and passion in development. This is an excellent opportunity for a talented developer looking to expand their experience in web application development.

The role:
You'll be working on the full process of the projects from beginning to the end and could get involved in all of the steps of creating the apps. As a boutique web app development company, we have a clear objective: to create innovative and bespoke web apps to elevate businesses.
As a Full-stack Junior developer you will use ReactJS as Front End technology, and Ruby on Rails as the Back End Technology.

You don't have experience or knowledge in any of these 2 technologies? You will be trained on both from scratch since the first day with our training program, and you will receive support from the rest of the team to keep growing on your Developer career.

Essential experience:
- Proven experience in web app development, or degree-level training in software development
 
Desirable experience:
- Development using MVC pattern
- HTML/CSS/JS
- Experience with: Database engines, Docker and Git version management
 
Our ideal candidate will be:
- Honest and straight forward
- Have the ability to adapt to new challenges
- Great at problem solving
 
What we offer:
- Friendly and supportive team.
- Office in central Barcelona with easy access via public transport.
- Flexible holidays.
- Training plan in both technologies.
- Career plan to grow with us.
- We have a range of opportunities ranging from a part time role, compatible with university studies or a young family up to a full-time role. We are looking for people who have long-term residency in Barcelona and who are fluent in English.</p><ul class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-list"><li nuevo)">(Publicada de nuevo)</span></div></li></ul><p class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-description ij-OfferCardContent-description-description--hideOnMobile">Software Engineer

redborder is a growing company as part of Innovalia Group currently working in customer projects involving trending technologies such as Cybersecurity, Big Data, and IoT. We are building dedicated teams of qualified IT engineers that can work developing and improving an entire end-to-end solution. Would you like to join us?

Your job
·You will be part of an agile team.

·You will analyze customer requirements, perform feasibility studies, provide technical proposal, estimate workload and contribute to features specification.

·You will participate in the design, implementation, security and validation of applications within a project team structure.

·You will collaborate in the documentation related to these activities.

·You will contribute to the full development cycle from design, planning, implementation, deployment and live operations

·You will explore and learn new technologies, and contributing to best practices already in place

Must-haves
·Degree in Computer Engineering or similar

·Solid background designing / developing software ideally with experience as a full stack developer

·Fluent in English (Minimum B2/C1)

·Comfortable working in a team environment with distributed version control (Git)

·Experience with modern software engineering best practices: unit testing/test automation, Continuous Integration, Test-Drive-Development.

·Main Languages/technologies: Java, HTML5, JavaScript, Ruby-On-Rails, Apache Kafka, Phyton, No SQL Database

Nice-to-haves
· Scrum certifications is a plus

The person that will fit our team should be:

· Team focused, highly collaborative 
  
·  Proactive, efficient and flexible

· Communicative

· Customer and results oriented

· Committed to her/his work, responsible for meeting deadlines and in continuous training of latest technologies.

· With great ability to work in a team

What we're offering
· Contract: Indefinite contract

· Type of working day: Full time. Monday to Friday

· Work in very innovative markets / technologies

·Opportunity to work with international clients</p><ul class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-list"><li class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-list-item class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-description ij-OfferCardContent-description-description--hideOnMobile">En PER SÉ Recursos humanos (www.perserrhh.com) estamos buscando Fronted Developer para incorporarse a nuestro cliente, compañía de producto líder de en el desarrollo de plataforma SaaS con fuerte componente de big data, retail, consultoría, marketing e ingeniería. 

¿Qué ofrecemos?

·	Incorporarte a un equipo joven y dinámico dentro de empresa tecnológica en pleno crecimiento. 
·	Centro de trabajo en Gijón, con modelo híbrido, pudiendo teletrabajar hasta 4 días a la semana.
·	Día de cumpleaños libre.
·	Plan de carrera y desarrollo de carrera profesional.
·	Salario acorde al perfil de la persona.
·	Contrato indefinido.

¿Qué buscamos?

Buscamos sumar un experto/a en frontend, aunque sin miedo a echar un ojo al backend.

Responsabilidades

·	Participarás en el desarrollo frontend de la nueva arquitectura. También interactuarás con la parte backend.
·	Implementarás nuevas funcionalidades dentro del frontend y mejorarás aquellas que ya están funcionando.
·	Recogerás -de forma estructurada- feedback de usuarios, clientes, desarrolladores, compañeros y el resto de actores que interactúen con el producto.
·	Contribuirás a desarrollar una nueva metodología de test para el frontend.
·	Priorizarás los ítems dentro de un roadmap que gestionarás teniendo en cuenta el coste/valor de los mismos y la estrategia de la compañía.
·	Te responsabilizarás de la entrega de nuevas funcionalidades y actualizaciones, ajustando el contexto y alcance -si fuera necesario- para entregar valor lo antes posible.</p><ul ij-FormatterSincedate--xs" data-testid="sincedate-tag">20 dic</span></li></ul><p class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-description ij-OfferCardContent-description-description--hideOnMobile">Desde nuestra empresa Tecnobit buscamos a una persona que quiera unirse a nuestro equipo de Valdepeñas (Ciudad Real). ¡No dudes en inscribirte!

Estamos seleccionando para participar en nuestro programa de becas remuneradas a un/a estudiante para formarse y adquirir conocimientos y experiencia en el desarrollo de Software, permitiendo adquirir experiencia en la integración de aplicaciones distribuidas, interfaces, y conocimiento sobre el funcionamiento de herramientas y metodologías ágiles. En concreto, las funciones a realizar durante la beca serán:

- Implementar, documentar y mantener la herramienta para la gestión de tareas de los proyectos.

- Gestión de código fuente, requisitos, pruebas y diseño utilizando las herramientas de la compañía.

-Generación de las métricas de control.

Las prácticas tendrán una duración de 6 meses con posibilidad real de contratación. Se realizarán de forma presencial en nuestras oficinas de Valdepeñas con una jornada de 7 horas / día en Turno de Mañana.

Grupo Oesía es una multinacional española dedicada a la ingeniería tecnológica y digital con más de 3.200 profesionales, que desarrollan e implementan proyectos en 25 países, generando empleo de calidad y formación continua en carreras técnicas.

Con 45 años de trayectoria, innova en productos y servicios que benefician a más de 2.000 millones de personas de todo el mundo, brindando soluciones en sanidad, administraciones públicas, defensa y seguridad, telecomunicaciones y alta tecnología, finanzas, logística, agroalimentación, automoción, aeronáutica y espacio.

¿Qué te ofrecemos?

- Trabajar en una multinacional, reconocida por Forbes como Mejor Empresa para Trabajar 2022, con múltiples oportunidades de desarrollo.

- Proyectos tecnológicos estables e innovadores para clientes punteros de ámbito nacional e internacional.

- Los días de nochebuena y fin de año no se trabajan .

- Horario flexible y jornada intensiva los meses de verano. Además de teletrabajo para una mejor conciliación.

- Plan de carrera: ofrecemos una atractiva carrera profesional en función de la experiencia y potencial personal dentro de una compañía en continua evolución y con un sólido crecimiento.

- Acceso gratuito a varias plataformas de formación para que tengas acceso a un amplio catálogo multidisciplinar .

- Tener acceso a una plataforma de descuentos en diferentes ámbitos.

- La igualdad de oportunidades y la diversidad dentro del equipo, así como el fomento de la inserción laboral de las mujeres y la adecuada integración de las personas con discapacidad son algunos de nuestros compromisos.</p><ul class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-list"><li class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-list-item ij-OfferCardContent-description-list-item--hideOnMobile">Contrato ij-OfferCardContent-description-description--hideOnMobile">Merlin Digital Partner is a tailor-made digital recruitment company for startups, scale-ups and corporates. We were born in Tech Barcelona where we established one of our main offices.

We are a dynamic and young team, tech & digital lovers, and truly committed with our candidates. We really believe in long-term relationships and not only in technical matches, so that we become the best brand ambassador for our partners.

We are currently looking for a Tech Lead Database

Our partner, with HQ in N.Y and BCN is the technology platform for digital magazines, which proposes a new reading experience on any device. 

They have grown a lot with 750M digital magazine editions, in 200 countries to over 10M customers. 

Role

Know several technologies and which one to use for the right thing. 
You enjoy building solutions for data management and even better if you do it with a wonderful team working together, learning from them, and teaching them alike.
Enjoy taking on difficult challenges where the limitations are not always necessarily technical, traveling around different teams and priorities.
Coordinate and synchronize with other teams to be aligned and solve dependencies
Have experience battling in high-availability projects, scalable, and big complex Databases.
You feel confident leading teams by teaching with example and mentoring best practices, all with a reduced ego and learning attitude.
Have absolutely zero problems communicating yourself in English.
 

We need: 

+5 years of experience with these technologies:

Linux administration.
SQL and NoSQL strong skills with proven experience in MySQL and at least one of the following technologies: Percona, PostgreSQL, Redis, Elasticsearch, MongoDB, or DocumentDB.
Cloud-native AWS (Amazon) or GCE. Experience with managed solutions, and knowledge of when to apply which one is highly valued

We  value:

Experience with: Python, Bash, Ruby.
Experience with Docker or container concept highly valued.
Prior experience provisioning and configuration management using; Terraform, Chef, Puppet, or Ansible highly valued.
We offer:

The opportunity to work in a multicultural environment and manage a world-class team.
Training budget.
Flexible schedule and working from home.
Flexible salary plan (health insurance, meal, and public transportation cards).
Fresh fruit, tea & good (unlimited) coffee. 

You will love working with them because: 

They lead the sector of their activity and they are always facing challenging new projects.
They are a technology company, and they invest in technology!
They have a highly skilled team so you can learn from your colleagues: knowledge sharing is strongly encouraged and lived. 
They do team tech meetups now and then to investigate promising technologies.
Training budget for those books and courses that will benefit you.
Agile/ Scrum way of working and philosophy.
You will be part of a multicultural team, working with different countries and time zones.
They have a fun, friendly & international work environment.

We offer a competitive salary package and a flexible salary plan, including:

Health Insurance Program.
Meal, Public Transportation Card & Nursery.
Training budget for teams. Books, meetups, you name it.
We also offer great benefits, including:
Full remote and also open space office in Barcelona with awesome views and fresh fruit, tea & good (unlimited) coffee.
Team-building activities.
Free digital magazines.</p><ul class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-list"><li class="ij-OfferCardContent-description-list-item ij-OfferCardContent-description-list-item--hideOnMobile">Contrato
